import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15, 10))
    sns.boxplot(x="country", y="life_expect", data=data, ax=ax)
    ax.set_xlabel("Country", fontsize=14)
    ax.set_ylabel("Life Expectancy", fontsize=14)
    ax.set_title("What is the distribution of life expectancy across different countries?", fontsize=16)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='life_expect', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of life expectancy over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['pop'])
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='pop', hue='cluster', multiple='stack', kde=False)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across different clusters?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Cluster')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="cluster", y="life_expect", data=data, ci=None)
    ax.axhline(y=data['life_expect'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the average life expectancy of each cluster?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Cluster')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
